  "prompt": "What is a market mechanism?",
  "response": "A market mechanism is a system by which the prices of goods and services are determined through the interaction of supply and demand in a free market economy. Key characteristics include:\n\n1. Market participants:\n- Buyers (consumers)\n- Sellers (producers)\n- Independent decision-makers\n\n2. Core principles:\n- Voluntary exchange\n- Price signals\n- Competition\n- Self-regulation\n\n3. Functions:\n- Allocating resources efficiently\n- Determining prices\n- Balancing supply and demand\n- Encouraging economic competition\n\n4. Key components:\n- Supply (amount of goods available)\n- Demand (consumer desire for goods)\n- Price\n- Market equilibrium\n\n5. Mechanisms of adjustment:\n- When demand increases, prices rise\n- When supply increases, prices fall\n- Prices act as signals for production and consumption decisions\n\n6. Advantages:\n- Promotes economic efficiency\n- Encourages innovation\n- Responds quickly to changing conditions\n- Minimizes government intervention\n\n7. Limitations:\n- Potential market failures\n- Unequal distribution of resources\n- Externalities\n- Information asymmetry\n\nA market mechanism allows economic actors to make decentralized decisions that collectively determine resource allocation and pricing.",
